<subSubSection id="C30EA6C4FFD4FF84CCF49137FBB63E4D" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BABF54FFFD4FF84CCF49137FC6A3CFC" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B960295DFFD4FF84CCF49137FEE73C60" bold="true" box="[151,297,258,283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">Description.</emphasis>
Vertex brownish yellow, with pair of milky yellow preapical spots medially. Eyes black (Figs D, E). Face brownish yellow (Fig. F). Pronotum pale yellow, with central part translucent, revealing three large black spots on mesonotum (Fig. D). Scutellum with apex and basal triangles black (Fig. D). Fore wing yellowish white, clavus with continuous dark brown vitta parallel to suture (Figs D, 
<number id="3DDCE768FFD4FF84CFE5915AFC5B3CFC" box="[902,917,367,391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" value="8.0">8</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABF54FFFD4FF84CCA491A7FC013CD0" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,967]" box="[199,975,402,427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">
Male abdominal apodemes small, not surpassing 
<number id="3DDCE768FFD4FF84CE8D91A7FD343CD0" box="[750,762,402,427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" value="3.0">3</number>
rd sternite (
<figureCitation id="132FE9CAFFD4FF84CF1F91A7FC0F3CD0" box="[892,961,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[160,1402,504,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,483,1868]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 15. Arboridia ochracea Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 8, Fore wing; 9, Abdominal apodemes; 10, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 11, Subgenital plate; 12, Style; 13, Aedeagus, lateral view; 14, Aedeagus, ventral view; 15, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238917/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDCE768FFD4FF84CFD291A6FC0F3CD0" box="[945,961,403,427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABF54FFFD4FF84CCA49183FC223FB0" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B960295DFFD4FF84CCA49183FEBE3CB4" box="[199,368,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer dorsal appendage simple, shallowly bifurcate at apex (
<figureCitation id="132FE9CAFFD4FF84C80C9183FB093CB4" box="[1135,1223,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[160,1402,504,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,483,1868]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 15. Arboridia ochracea Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 8, Fore wing; 9, Abdominal apodemes; 10, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 11, Subgenital plate; 12, Style; 13, Aedeagus, lateral view; 14, Aedeagus, ventral view; 15, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238917/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDCE768FFD4FF84C8CB9182FB093CB4" box="[1192,1223,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate without basolateral angulate projection, with 
<number id="3DDCE768FFD4FF84CEF791EEFD6C3C88" box="[660,674,475,499]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" value="4.0">4</number>
macrosetae in oblique row and row of short rigid setae along upper margin; apical 
<number id="3DDCE768FFD4FF84CD2591CAFE9F3F6C" box="[326,337,511,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DDCE768FFD4FF84CD3F91CAFEA53F6C" box="[348,363,511,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" value="3.0">3</number>
, with dark color (
<figureCitation id="132FE9CAFFD4FF84CE2391CBFD5B3F6C" box="[576,661,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[160,1402,504,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,483,1868]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 15. Arboridia ochracea Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 8, Fore wing; 9, Abdominal apodemes; 10, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 11, Subgenital plate; 12, Style; 13, Aedeagus, lateral view; 14, Aedeagus, ventral view; 15, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238917/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDCE768FFD4FF84CE1491CAFD5B3F6C" box="[631,661,511,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Style long, with 
<number id="3DDCE768FFD4FF84CF1391CAFCB03F6C" box="[880,894,511,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" value="2.0">2</number>
sharp points at apex; preapical lobe small but distinct (
<figureCitation id="132FE9CAFFD4FF84CC9F9217FE9C3F40" box="[252,338,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[160,1402,504,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,483,1868]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 15. Arboridia ochracea Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 8, Fore wing; 9, Abdominal apodemes; 10, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 11, Subgenital plate; 12, Style; 13, Aedeagus, lateral view; 14, Aedeagus, ventral view; 15, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238917/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDCE768FFD4FF84CD509216FE9C3F40" box="[307,338,547,571]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with two pairs of processes arising from apex and base of shaft respectively, basal processes short, slender and closely appressed on ventral surface of shaft, distal processes approximately same length but arising laterad of gonopore and extended posterolaterad; aedeagal shaft long, only median area slightly bent ventrad; gonopore large, apical on ventral surface; preatrium much longer than dorsal apodeme, evenly curved in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="132FE9CAFFD4FF84CD259287FE063FB0" box="[326,456,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[160,1402,504,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,483,1868]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 15. Arboridia ochracea Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 8, Fore wing; 9, Abdominal apodemes; 10, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 11, Subgenital plate; 12, Style; 13, Aedeagus, lateral view; 14, Aedeagus, ventral view; 15, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238917/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">Figs 13, 14</figureCitation>
). Connective robust, broadly V-shaped (
<figureCitation id="132FE9CAFFD4FF84CFE89287FC113FB0" box="[907,991,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[160,1402,504,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,483,1868]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 15. Arboridia ochracea Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 8, Fore wing; 9, Abdominal apodemes; 10, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 11, Subgenital plate; 12, Style; 13, Aedeagus, lateral view; 14, Aedeagus, ventral view; 15, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238917/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDCE768FFD4FF84CFA39287FC113FB0" box="[960,991,690,715]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABF54FFFD4FF84CCA492E3FBAD3F94" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,967]" box="[199,1123,726,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B960295DFFD4FF84CCA492E3FEBC3F94" bold="true" box="[199,370,726,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">Measurement.</emphasis>
Body length males 
<quantity id="4CEC58AAFFD4FF84CE3192E2FD153F95" box="[594,731,727,751]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" unit="mm" value="3.25" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.3 mm</quantity>
, females 
<number id="3DDCE768FFD4FF84CF2692E2FC563F94" box="[837,920,727,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" value="3.3499999999999996" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.4</number>
(including wing).
</paragraph>
