<subSubSection id="C30EA6C4FFD4FF84CCA49377FB2F3E04" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BABF54FFFD4FF84CCA49377FB2F3E04" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B960295DFFD4FF84CCA49377FEF53E20" bold="true" box="[199,315,834,859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species can be distinguished from other species of the genus by its unique aedeagus, which has two pairs of processes arising from apex and base of aedeagal shaft respectively (
<figureCitation id="132FE9CAFFD4FF84C8319353FB1D3E04" box="[1106,1235,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[160,1402,504,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,483,1868]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 15. Arboridia ochracea Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 8, Fore wing; 9, Abdominal apodemes; 10, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 11, Subgenital plate; 12, Style; 13, Aedeagus, lateral view; 14, Aedeagus, ventral view; 15, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238917/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">Figs 13, 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30EA6C4FFD4FF84CCA493BFFD5E3EBC" pageId="4" pageNumber="588" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BABF54FFFD4FF84CCA493BFFD5E3EBC" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B960295DFFD4FF84CCA493BFFE803ED8" bold="true" box="[199,334,906,931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin word “ 
<emphasis id="B960295DFFD4FF84CFFD93BFFBDF3ED8" box="[926,1041,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="588">ochraceus</emphasis>
”, referring to the fore wing clavus with continuous orange-brown vitta (Fig. D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
